ence%2C%20saying%20punishments%20may%20go%20as%20far%20as%20the%20death%20penalty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETop%20legal%20bodies%20in%20the%20country%20%E2%80%94%20including%20its%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20national%20prosecutors%2C%20and%20three%20government%20ministries%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.spp.gov.cn%2Fxwfbh%2Fwsfbt%2F202406%2Ft20240621_657405.shtml%232%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejointly%20issued%20a%20statement%3C%2Fa%3E%20telling%20courts%20and%20prosecutors%20at%20all%20levels%20in%20China%20to%20%26quot%3Bseverely%20punish%20'Taiwan%20independence'%20diehards.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20are%20China's%20first%20official%20guidelines%20designating%20support%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-warning-companies-supporting-financing-taiwan-independence-2021-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETaiwan's%20independence%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20a%20crime%2C%20underscoring%20how%20Beijing%20is%20hardening%20its%20stance%20toward%20the%20self-governed%20island.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETaiwan%20declaring%20independence%20has%20long%20been%20a%20red%20line%20set%20by%20Beijing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBroad%20definitions%20of%20the%20crimes%20include%20promoting%20the%20idea%20of%20%26quot%3Btwo%20Chinas%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Bone%20China%2C%20one%20Taiwan%26quot%3B%20and%20creating%20an%20organization%20that%20tries%20to%20attain%20Taiwan's%20independence.%20Relying%20on%20%26quot%3Bforeign%20forces%26quot%3B%20and%20institutions%20to%20achieve%20independence%20was%20also%20listed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENotably%2C%20the%20list%20criminalizes%20public%20attempts%20to%20undermine%20the%20concept%20that%20Taiwan%20is%20part%20of%20China%20in%20the%20%26quot%3Bfields%20of%20education%2C%20culture%2C%20history%2C%20news%20media%2C%20etc.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20punishments%20include%20prison%20sentences%20or%20detention%20of%20up%20to%2010%20years%2C%20with%20that%20limit%20removed%20for%20those%20leading%20organiz