0it's%20setting%20up%20with%20him%20leaving%2C%20are%20great%20for%20us%20to%20get%20a%20bit%20of%20Daemon's%20interiority.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECaralynn%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Also%20the%20chemistry%20between%20Matt%20and%20Emma%20is%20absolute%20fire%2C%20as%20usual.%20They're%20both%20top%20of%20their%20games%20in%20that%20scene.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAyomikun%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20This%20conversation%20also%20sees%20them%20finally%20confronting%20an%20issue%20that%20we%2C%20as%20viewers%2C%20have%20all%20wanted%20to%20see%20hashed%20out%20since%20Daemon%20first%20started%20trying%20to%20romance%20Rhaenyra.%20Does%20he%20actually%20care%20for%20her%2C%20or%20is%20she%20another%20obstacle%20to%20what%20he%20really%20wants%3A%20power%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPalmer%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20It's%20refreshing%20to%20see%20Rhaenyra%20basically%20hit%20her%20breaking%20point%20there.%20I%20think%20it's%20important%20to%20note%20that%20she's%20been%20using%20him%20as%20well%2C%20whether%20it%20was%20to%20maybe%20indirectly%20piss%20off%20Viserys%2C%20or%20more%20obviously%2C%20to%20strengthen%20her%20standing%20as%20heir.%20This%20is%20the%20moment%20where%20she%20realizes%20that%20he's%20more%20of%20a%20liability%20than%20a%20boon%2C%20and%20that%20the%20challenge%20of%20mentally%20sparring%20with%20him%20just%20isn't%20worth%20it%20anymore.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECaralynn%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20I%20love%20that%20Rhaenyra%20lays%20every%20single%20card%20out%20on%20the%20table%20here.%20She's%20had%20enough%20of%20Daemon%20and%20his%20games.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPalmer%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20It%20speaks%20volumes%20that%20his%20insult%20is%20instead%20that%20Viserys%20used%20her%20to%20get%20back%20at%20him%2C%20by%20naming%20her%20as%20the%20heir.%20Daemon%20still%20ultimately%20sees%20her%20as%20a%20pawn%2C%20rather%20than%20a%20player.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAyomikun%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Also%2C%20though%20I%20do%20believe%20both%20Aegon%20and%20D